OL,4,CLondon's mayor have more power?
OL,6,FHe added: "I think the argument has
OL,7,Fgot to be made really strongly by all
OL,8,Fparts of London, by politicians, by
OL,9,Fbusiness, by civil society, is that in
OL,10,Fvery straitened times where tax levels
OL,11,Fare high, when public services are
OL,12,Fsqueezed, devolving more spending to
OL,13,Flocal government to London government
OL,14,Fwill deliver both better spend.
OL,16,F"So we'll get better bang for our
OL,17,Fbuck, we'll get better public services
OL,18,Fand will also enable us prioritize to
OL,19,Fspend on the things that can really
OL,20,Fshift the dial on jobs and growth in
OL,21,FLondon.
