OL,3,CMore 'bang for our buck': Should
OL,4,CLondon's mayor have more power?
OL,6,F"I think the central priority any
OL,7,Fmayor will face is having the
OL,8,Fresources to deliver against the big
OL,9,Fchallenges the city faces that they're
OL,10,Fresponsible for - housing, transport,
OL,11,Fcrime, policing.
OL,13,F"And so getting the resources, getting
OL,14,Fcontrol over resources in London must
OL,15,Fbe the central priority for any
OL,16,Fincoming mayor."
OL,18,FMaking the case for more powers is
OL,19,Fnothing new and successive mayors have
OL,20,Falready made the case.
