OL,3,CMore 'bang for our buck': Should
OL,4,CLondon's mayor have more power?
OL,6,FWith other mayors in other parts of
OL,7,Fthe UK having more power in some areas
OL,8,Fit's likely whoever wins the London
OL,9,Fmayoral election on 2 May may want a
OL,10,Fwider remit.
OL,12,FDevolution can bring with it the
OL,13,Fbenefits of making political decisions
OL,14,Fthat work for people locally, such as
OL,15,Fthe introduction of the Oyster card in
OL,16,FLondon.
OL,18,FPolicing can also be more localized if
OL,19,Fpolicy set locally which allows a more
OL,20,Fnuanced local approach to fit local
OL,21,Fcircumstances, campaigners argue.
